# DevOps CLI Tool Implementation Plan

A modular command-line interface tool that provides a unified interface for common DevOps operations including server management, deployment, backup, monitoring, and log analysis.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Structure

```
/home/hsf/Noob_Dev/devops-cli/
├── devops-cli              # Main executable script
├── modules/                # Command modules directory
│   ├── server.sh          # Server management commands
│   ├── deploy.sh          # Deployment commands
│   ├── backup.sh          # Backup operations
│   ├── monitor.sh         # Monitoring commands
│   └── logs.sh            # Log management
├── lib/                   # Shared libraries
│   ├── config.sh          # Configuration management
│   ├── logger.sh          # Logging system
│   └── helpers.sh         # Common helper functions
└── COMMANDS.md            # Command documentation
```

---

### Core Components

#### [NEW] [devops-cli](file:///home/hsf/Noob_Dev/devops-cli/devops-cli)
Main entry point script that:
- Parses command-line arguments
- Routes to appropriate module
- Handles global options (--help, --version, --config)
- Initializes configuration and logging

#### [NEW] [lib/config.sh](file:///home/hsf/Noob_Dev/devops-cli/lib/config.sh)
Configuration management system:
- Creates and manages `~/.devops-cli/config`
- Provides functions to read/write configuration
- Handles default values
- Validates configuration options

#### [NEW] [lib/logger.sh](file:///home/hsf/Noob_Dev/devops-cli/lib/logger.sh)
Logging system with rotation:
- Logs to `~/.devops-cli/logs/devops-cli.log`
- Implements log rotation (size-based)
- Provides log levels (DEBUG, INFO, WARN, ERROR)
- Timestamps all log entries

#### [NEW] [lib/helpers.sh](file:///home/hsf/Noob_Dev/devops-cli/lib/helpers.sh)
Common utility functions:
- Error handling functions
- Input validation
- Color output for terminal
- Common checks (root access, dependencies, etc.)

---

### Command Modules

#### [NEW] [modules/server.sh](file:///home/hsf/Noob_Dev/devops-cli/modules/server.sh)
Server management commands:
- `start` - Start server/service
- `stop` - Stop server/service
- `restart` - Restart server/service
- `status` - Check server status
- `list` - List available servers

#### [NEW] [modules/deploy.sh](file:///home/hsf/Noob_Dev/devops-cli/modules/deploy.sh)
Deployment commands:
- `app` - Deploy application
- `rollback` - Rollback to previous version
- `status` - Check deployment status
- `list` - List deployments

#### [NEW] [modules/backup.sh](file:///home/hsf/Noob_Dev/devops-cli/modules/backup.sh)
Backup operations:
- `create` - Create new backup
- `restore` - Restore from backup
- `list` - List available backups
- `delete` - Delete old backups

#### [NEW] [modules/monitor.sh](file:///home/hsf/Noob_Dev/devops-cli/modules/monitor.sh)
Monitoring commands:
- `cpu` - Monitor CPU usage
- `memory` - Monitor memory usage
- `disk` - Monitor disk usage
- `network` - Monitor network stats
- `services` - Monitor service health

#### [NEW] [modules/logs.sh](file:///home/hsf/Noob_Dev/devops-cli/modules/logs.sh)
Log management:
- `view` - View logs with filtering
- `tail` - Tail logs in real-time
- `search` - Search logs for patterns
- `rotate` - Manually rotate logs
- `clean` - Clean old logs

